Well, there is a difference between &quot;format specifier&quot; and &quot;format string&quot;. The first argument to printf is the format string, the `%d` and `%s` type things are the format specifiers. I was talking about this<p><pre><code>    printf(&quot;Hi&quot;, 45);
</code></pre>
which will not segfault. If you meant<p><pre><code>    printf(45);
</code></pre>
Then you are absolutely correct, that would segfault on common machines.
